<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-15 00:06 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mavericks 111, Pacers 90  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS (AP) -- Dirk Nowitzki scored 28 points -- 13 during a 15-0
run to open the second half -- and the Dallas Mavericks beat the
Indiana Pacers 111-90 on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Nash added 21 points and Michael Finley had 16 points and
11 assists to help the Mavericks to their second-largest margin of
victory this season.
</P>
<P>
   Rookie Greg Buckner had 10 points and 11 rebounds for the
Mavericks, his first career double-double.
</P>
<P>
   Travis Best led Indiana with 26 points and Jalen Rose added 18
points and 13 rebounds. Austin Croshere had 10 points and 13
rebounds for the Eastern Division-leading Pacers.
</P>
<P>
   Reggie Miller had only seven points, 12 under his team-leading
average and just one better than his lowest scoring game this
season. Miller has been bothered by a bruised right quad and was
listed as questionable for the game.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas took a 36-18 first-quarter lead and was in front by as
many as 20 in the second quarter. Best scored 15 points in the
second quarter to keep the Pacers within range, but Dallas held a
60-46 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks maintained first-half momentum by opening the
third quarter with 15 straight points, including three 3-pointers
by Nowitzki, for a 75-46 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Indiana, which had won four of its previous five games, failed
to score over the first four minutes of the third quarter until
Croshere's follow.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas went on to lead by as many as 32 points in the third
quarter and took an 86-61 advantage into the final quarter.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Mavericks hired Brad Davis as an assistant coach. The
team hired former Lakers coach Del Harris as their defensive
coordinator on Monday. Davis will assist Harris as the Mavericks
attempt to improve a defense that was allowing 103.1 points per
game entering Tuesday night, third-worst in the league. ... The
Mavericks also are talking to Gar Heard about an assistant's
position. Heard was coach of the Mavericks in the 1992-93 season.
He was fired as coach of the Washington Wizards this season. ...
The Mavericks activated center Bruno Sundov off the injured list.
... Indiana's Dale Davis missed the game with leg cramps.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
