<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Suns 107, Timberwolves 100  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- Penny Hardaway scored a game-high 26 points and
the Phoenix Suns hit 24 fourth-quarter free throws to beat the
Minnesota Timberwolves 107-100 Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Hardaway was 12-for-12 from the line for the Suns, who won for
the sixth time in seven games and kept pace with San Antonio in the
Western Conference playoff race.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix trails the Spurs by a half-game for fourth place and
home-court advantage in the first round.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns were a season-high 43-of-49 from the free-throw line,
including 24-of-27 in the fourth quarter. Three Timberwolves fouled
out as Minnesota was whistled for 34 fouls, 16 in the final period.
</P>
<P>
   Cliff Robinson added 24 points, five capping a 9-0 run that gave
the Suns their first lead since midway through the first quarter.
Rodney Rogers had 16 points for Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   Terrell Brandon led the Timberwolves with 18 points, but was
held scoreless over the final 21 minutes. Kevin Garnett missed 10
of his first 13 shots and finished with 17 points.
</P>
<P>
   Malik Sealy and Wally Szczerbiak each had 13 for Minnesota,
which saw its franchise-record five-game road winning streak end.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns went more than three minutes without a field goal
midway through the fourth quarter, but converted 11 straight free
throws to take control.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson was fouled by Szczerbiak while shooting a 3-pointer and
hit all three free throws to give Phoenix an 86-82 lead with 6:01
left. Szczerbiak made consecutive baskets to tie the game, but the
Suns went on a 10-0 run -- all but two coming from the free-throw
line -- to take a 96-86 lead with 2:42 left.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix shot 40.9 percent from the floor in the first half, but
trailed only 51-47 with the help of some uncharacteristically
sloppy play by the Timberwolves.
</P>
<P>
   Minnesota, which entered the game averaging an NBA-low 13.8
turnovers per game, gave the ball away 10 times in each half.
</P>
<P>
   Anthony Peeler converted a three-point play as Minnesota
stretched its lead to 58-53 with 8:54 left in the third quarter.
Robinson rallied the Suns, scoring off a tip-in and adding a
3-pointer as Phoenix took a 62-58 lead with 6:50 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Robinson's 3-pointer was one of only two for the Suns on 13
attempts.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Suns have won 11 of their last 12 home games. ...
Phoenix, which won the first 25 meetings between the teams and 27
of the first 28, beat Minnesota for just the sixth time in the last
14 games. ... Garnett has averaged 14.3 points (19-for-58), 8.7
below his season average, in the Timberwolves' three games against
Phoenix this season. ... Suns guard Rex Chapman (back spasms) did
not dress. Chapman has missed 10 games this season through injury
or suspension. ... Timberwolves forward Sam Mitchell missed his
13th straight game with a sprained left ankle.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
