<HEADLINE> Clippers 110, Nuggets 106  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Eric Piatkowski scored a career-high 31
points and Lamar Odom got 13 of his 25 points in the final six
minutes as the Los Angeles Clippers rallied to stun the Denver
Nuggets 110-106 on Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
   Derek Anderson added 20 points the Clippers, who rallied from 14
point down in the fourth quarter. They have won back-to-back games
for the first time since late December after ending a 19-game road
losing streak Monday night against Golden State. The win was only
the fourth for Los Angeles in its last 37 games.
</P>
<P>
   Antonio McDyess had 31 points and Chris Gatling added 19 for the
Nuggets, who have lost a season-worst seven straight and have
dropped their last 13 road games against Pacific Division
opponents.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 92-78 with 10:27 to play, the Clippers outscored Denver
17-9 over the next five minutes. The Clippers capped the rally with
Odom's 3-pointer and driving layup.
</P>
<P>
   Los Angeles got within two points on a 13-footer by Derek
Anderson and Piatkowski's steal led to a three-point play by
Anderson for a 102-101 edge with 3:13 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   George McCloud's 19-footer gave the Nuggets their last lead,
103-102. Anderson made one of two free throws and Odom followed
with a 3-pointer.
</P>
<P>
   The play that killed the Nuggets was an offensive charge by
McDyess, who earned a technical foul with 1:04 left. Piatkowski
converted the free throw and Odom sank three foul shots in the
final minute.
</P>
<P>
   The Nuggets lost despite shooting 57 percent from the field.
They committed 21 turnovers.
</P>
<P>
   The Clippers tied the score at 70 on Maurice Taylor's short
jumper with 5:38 left in the third. The Nuggets responded with a
9-2 spurt that included seven points by Van Exel.
</P>
<P>
   McDyess, the Clippers' second overall pick in the 1995 draft --
he never played a game for them -- converted a three-point play with
three seconds left in the period for an 86-75 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The teams ended the first half tied at 55. After Keon Clark
scored the game's first basket, the Nuggets fell behind by as many
as nine points. They didn't lead again until rookie Chris Herren's
driving layup gave them a 36-35 edge with 7 1-2 minutes left in the
second quarter. Piatkowski, who scored 11 points in the first 5:48
of the game, hit a game-tying 21-footer with seven seconds left in
the half.
</P>
<P>
Notes: The Nuggets have won only two of their last 44 road games
against Pacific Division teams since Jan. 7, 1997 -- and both
victories have been against the Clippers. ... McCloud, coming off a
season-high 25 points at Orlando, returned to the Nuggets lineup
after serving a one-game suspension for his post-game altercation
with Magic guard Ron Mercer on Saturday night. ... Guard Jeff
McInnis, a former second-round draft pick by the Nuggets whose
second 10-day contract with the Clippers expired on Tuesday, was
re-signed by Los Angeles through the end of next season.
</P>
</TEXT>
