<DATE_TIME> 2000-03-15 01:38 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nia Long Talks To Essence Magazine  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Nia Long says watching her single mother
struggle to support the pair when she was growing up gave her the
drive she needed to succeed as an actress.
</P>
<P>
   ''My motivation to be successful was the conviction that we
couldn't live like that forever, not knowing how we were going to
pay the bills,'' says Long, who was raised in Los Angeles. ''My
mother was on welfare, working a job under the table until she made
enough to get off of welfare.''
</P>
<P>
   Long's film credits include ''The Best Man'' and ''love jones.''
She currently stars in the movie ''Boiler Room'' with Giovanni
Ribisi and Ben Affleck.
</P>
<P>
   Long tells the April edition of Essence that acting is her
''most favorite thing'' in the world.
</P>
<P>
   ''That's what I live for. Acting is very therapeutic. It teaches
you not to be afraid of emotions.''
</P>
</TEXT>
