<HEADLINE> Celebrity Spotlight &AMP; Birthdays  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   In the birthday spotlight:
</P>
<P>
   ''Sex and the City'' star Sarah Jessica Parker won best comic
actress at this year's Golden Globe Awards. ''I've never won
anything in my life,'' exclaimed Parker after winning the award.
''I had money on all the nominees in my category because they're
all so good and talented.'' Parker, who is married to actor Matthew
Broderick, was born on March 25, 1965.
</P>
<P>
   Talk-show host Rosie O'Donnell recently adopted her third child,
Blake Christopher O'Donnell. O'Donnell, who is single, says she has
told her two older children that all families are different. ''They
have a clear understanding about who the people are in their family
and they have very strong male influences,'' says O'Donnell, who
was born on March 21, 1962.
</P>
<P>
   Comedian Louie Anderson says a grand gesture when he was
starting out 10 years ago got him his big break in show business.
He said it all began when actor-comedian Eddie Murphy walked into
an expensive Los Angeles restaurant. Anderson called the waiter
over and told him, ''Take Eddie Murphy's check and put it on my
credit card, but don't tell him until after I leave.'' The bill
came to $600, but the gesture paid off. Murphy phoned Anderson the
next day and said, ''Louie, no one ever did that for me.'' He then
told Anderson that he was going to write a part for him in the
movie ''Coming to America.'' Anderson was born on March 24, 1953.
</P>
<P>
   Celebrity birthdays for March 19-25:
</P>
<P>
   March 19: Actress Renee Taylor (''The Nanny'') is 65. Actress
Ursula Andress is 64. Musician Paul Atkinson of the Zombies is 54.
Singer Ruth Pointer of the Pointer Sisters is 54. Actress Glenn
Close is 53. Actor Bruce Willis is 45. Musician Gert Bettens of K's
Choice is 30.
</P>
<P>
   March 20: Producer Carl Reiner is 78. Children's TV-host Fred
Rogers is 72. Actor Hal Linden is 69. Actor William Hurt is 50.
Musician Carl Palmer of Emerson, Lake and Palmer is 50. Director
Spike Lee is 43. Actress Holly Hunter is 42. Musician Slim Jim
Phantom of the Stray Cats is 39. Actor Alexander Chaplin (''Spin
City'') is 29.
</P>
<P>
   March 21: Actor Timothy Dalton is 56. Singer-musician Rodger
Hodgson of Supertramp is 50. Musician Conrad Lozano of Los Lobos is
49. Actress Sabrina LeBeauf (''The Cosby Show'') is 42. Actor Gary
Oldman is 42. Actor Matthew Broderick is 38. Talk-show host Rosie
O'Donnell is 38. Musician Andrew Copeland of Sister Hazel is 32. DJ
Premier of Gang Starr is 31.
</P>
<P>
   March 22: Actor Karl Malden is 88. Actor William Shatner is 69.
Singer George Benson is 57. Actress Lena Olin is 45. Actor Matthew
Modine is 41. Actress Reese Witherspoon is 24.
</P>
<P>
   March 23: Singer Chaka Khan is 47. Actress Amanda Plummer is 43.
Actress Keri Russell (''Felicity'') is 24. Actress Nicholle Tom
(''The Nanny'') is 23.
</P>
