<HEADLINE> Federal-Mogul To Close Warehouses  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SOUTHFIELD, Mich. (AP) -- Federal-Mogul Corp. said Wednesday it
will close 25 North American facilities and cut 1,500 jobs in an
effort to improve the auto parts company's bottom line.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to shutting 23 warehouses and two factories, the
company plans to make changes at 19 other facilities in North and
South America and consolidate 18 manufacturing and distribution
operations in Europe and Asia.
</P>
<P>
   Federal-Mogul has not yet decided whether those changes would
involve closing or downsizing plants or moving product lines,
spokeswoman Kimberly A. Welch said Wednesday. The company has 170
plants worldwide, she said.
</P>
<P>
   The changes will cut Federal-Mogul's global workforce of 50,400
employees by about 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Federal-Mogul said costs related to the restructuring will
require about $100 million in charges against earnings over the
next two years, as well as an additional $100 million in
incremental expenses and capital expenditures.
</P>
<P>
   The reorganization will begin this year and will be completed by
the end of 2002, the company said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
