<HEADLINE> Dogs Kill 17-Year-Old Brazilian Boy  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAO PAULO, Brazil (AP) -- A 17-year-old-boy died Wednesday after
he was attacked by two Rottweiller dogs guarding a construction
site, according to media reports, marking the second fatal attack
by dogs this week.
</P>
<P>
   Andre Goncalves Dias was attacked on Monday when he and a friend
entered the site in Curitiba, 220 miles southwest of Sao Paulo, the
Agencia Folha news service reported.
</P>
<P>
   After the dogs attacked, area residents tried to save Dias by
throwing rocks. Police said officers responding to the call shot
and killed the animals.
</P>
<P>
   Dias' friend escaped unhurt, but Dias was severely bitten and
died of his wounds Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   On Sunday, six Rottweillers killed a 4-year-old girl and injured
her sister and their mother as they returned home from church in
Carapicuiba, a rural district on the outskirts of Sao Paulo.
</P>
<P>
   The dogs were apparently set loose earlier in the day to guard a
farm where the mother and the children's father live and work as
caretakers, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
