<HEADLINE> Ariz., Texas Execute Inmates  </HEADLINE>
By WALTER BERRY, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   FLORENCE, Ariz. (AP) -- A man who killed two armored-van guards
during a robbery that netted almost $300,000 was executed by
injection Wednesday, less than a year after his brother was also
put to death for the crimes.
</P>
<P>
   The execution of Patrick Poland was the first of two death
sentences carried out Wednesday. Texas executed confessed killer
Timothy Lane Gribble Wednesday evening, a day after the state held
another execution.
</P>
<P>
   In Arizona, Poland, 50, was pronounced dead at 3:07 p.m.,
minutes after he told relatives of his two victims he was ''sorry
for the pain and suffering I have caused.''
</P>
<P>
   He asked his girlfriend, who witnessed his death, ''to remember
I will always love her.''
</P>
<P>
   Poland and his brother, Michael, disguised themselves as highway
patrolmen and rented a car that resembled a police cruiser in 1977
before performing a traffic stop on the van.
</P>
<P>
   The van was ransacked of $288,000. The next day, prosecutors
said, the brothers placed guards Cecil Newkirk and Russell Dempsey
in canvas bags before dumping them into Lake Mead, 250 miles away.
</P>
<P>
   Authorities said the guards may have been alive at the time.
</P>
<P>
   The brothers were arrested in May 1978 after leaving a trail of
clues, including their spending $127,000 of the money in their
hometown of Prescott.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Poland was executed in June. He was 59. His brother's
execution on Wednesday was Arizona's 21st since the state resumed
capital punishment in 1992.
</P>
<P>
   In Texas, Gribble, 36, was put to death by injection shortly
after 6 p.m. for the 1987 abduction, rape and strangling of Donna
Weis, a Clear Lake Shores, Texas, city council member.
</P>
<P>
   Gribble led a lengthy final statement from the death chamber.
</P>
<P>
   ''I just want you to know from the bottom of my heart that I am
truly sorry,'' he said, looking toward witnesses. ''I mean it. I'm
not just saying it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
