<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-Bronco Smith Dies at Age 54  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Former defensive lineman Paul Smith, a member of
the Denver Broncos' famed ''Orange Crush'' defense, is dead. He was
54.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, who played 11 of his 13 seasons with the Broncos, died
Tuesday night after having battled with pancreatic cancer,
according to broadcast reports.
</P>
<P>
   Former Broncos coach John Ralston called Smith the ''finest
defensive tackle in pro football.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith played on Denver's 1978 Super Bowl team and was inducted
into the team's Ring of Fame in 1986.
</P>
<P>
   The University of New Mexico graduate made the Pro Bowl in 1972
and 1973, posting 11 quarterback sacks both seasons. He played his
final two seasons with the Washington Redskins.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
