<HEADLINE> Ventura Won't Endorse Bush, Gore  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WINONA, Minn. (AP) -- Neither Al Gore nor George W. Bush should
expect Jesse Ventura's endorsement without paying a price, the
Minnesota governor said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   To win him over, a candidate would ''have to sever from being a
Republican or Democrat,'' Ventura said during a forum on MSNBC's
''Hardball With Chris Matthews.''
</P>
<P>
   Ventura predicted that Sen. John McCain, who dropped from the
Republican race last week, would be elected president if he ran as
an independent. McCain has said he plans to stick with the GOP.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're a sucker for underdogs,'' Ventura said. ''We love in the
United States to cheer on Rocky Balboa who isn't given a chance to
win.''
</P>
<P>
   Matthews pressed Ventura several times on his own presidential
aspirations, but the independent governor said the chances that he
would ever run were ''slim to none. Much (closer) to none.''
</P>
