<HEADLINE> Fireworks Blast Kills 4 in Mexico  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- Sparks from a fireworks display apparently
fell on other fireworks, setting off an explosion that killed four
people, injured 15 and badly damaged a church on Wednesday,
officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The government's Notimex news agency quoted the Mexico State
attorney general's office as saying more than 1,700 fireworks blew
up in Santa Ana Jilotzingo during a religious festival celebrating
the end of a pilgrimage to a nearby shrine.
</P>
<P>
   It said eight of the injuries were serious, Notimex reported.
</P>
<P>
   Mexico City television stations broadcast images of the badly
damaged church against which the fireworks had been kept -- two of
its walls blown out and an interior scarred by flying debris.
</P>
<P>
   Santa Ana Jilotzingo is about 15 miles west of Mexico City.
</P>
</TEXT>
